  "title": "Structural Engineer",
  "description": "<p>Based in Singapore</p><p>RESPONSIBILITIES</p><p>· Assist the Team Directors in the performance of their duties</p><p>· Ensure quality and accuracy of designs</p><p>· Offer suggestions to improve the designs</p><p>· Produce sketch drawings</p><p>· Carry out design calculations</p><p>· Check design calculations</p><p>· Ensure compliance with Project Design Criteria/Client Brief/Approved Concept</p><p>· Ensure compliance with relevant design standards and office standards</p><p>· Check documentation complies with design</p><p>· Attend and participate in design meetings</p><p>· Ensure compliance with ISO Quality Procedure Manual</p><p><br /></p><p>Job Requirement</p><p>• Bachelor’s degree in Civil or Structural Engineering</p><p>• 1 - 3 years of design experience in a consulting environment. Fresh graduates will also be considered.</p><p>• Design experience in high rise residential, commercial or mixed development projects</p><p>• Project experience handling hospital, data centre, office projects will be advantageous</p><p>• Familiar and hands-on knowledge of the latest design software and European code</p><p>• Hands-on experience with the analysis and design of large building projects in structural steel, R.C. and post tensioned concrete</p>",
